&nbsp;AGI - Never been at risk the security of the premier. In a note the undersecretary of the Presidency of the Council, Alfredo Mantovano, in relation to the story of Andrea Giambruno and the hypothetical 007 surprised to encircle around the car of the former companion of Giorgia Meloni. "From the episode under the house of the President of the Council in the night between 30 November and 1 December, while President Meloni was engaged in a mission abroad - he wrote in a Mantovano note - I punctually reported, as delegated Authority for the Security of the Republic, in my last hearing at Copasir on 4 April last. I have no difficulty in reasserting what has already been clarified in my own parliamentary office, namely that the investigations carried out for the part of the intelligence department have allowed for sure to exclude the involvement in the episode of members of the Services, and that the security of President Meloni has never been put at risk." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
The episode to which Mantovano refers, which has the delegation to the secret services, was reported by the newspaper Tomorrow. The article reads that on that night between 30 November and 1 December 2023, that is more than a month after Meloni had announced the end of his relationship with Andrea Giambruno, outside the villa just purchased from the premier, in the area Roma Sud, there is the car of Giambruno. And a short distance away, as the security protocol provides, there's a police officer watching. The agents in service notice two people who are tinkering around the Giambruno car. The policemen, always according to what was reconstructed by tomorrow, approach and ask the generalities to the two men, who however would show a badge qualifying as 'colleges', and then dilegate.
&nbsp;
Afterwards, according to Tomorrow, a report was drawn up that reconstructed the incident, immediately delivered to Digos. The head of police Pisani, the Minister of the Interior of Piantedosi, Mantovano, the then head of the Aisi Parente and his right arm Del Deo, and also the premier. What were those men doing around the former Premier's car? They were looking for something? "Or worse still to place bedbugs or transponders to be able to spy on him," as tomorrow suggests? The report ended however in prosecution and the head of the Roman pm, Lo Voi, takes care of it firsthand.
&nbsp;
The first investigations are the agents of the Internal Information and Security Agency (Aisi), who work to identify the two men discovered around the car of Giambruno and to understand whether this episode was putting at risk or not the security of our institutions. "After a few days of work, thanks also to the description of the agent who had seen in the face men and to cross-checks of the police of Rome on some photographs, the possible suspects are identified tomorrow. Surprisingly, it is two secret agents in force to the Aisi, and that are part of the nourished escort of Meloni." Or better: two agents who had been excluded from the team protecting the premier.
&nbsp;
"The investigation goes on for two months, but at some point the Aisi backs against what was initially suggested on the men of the escort," reads again in the article: the telephone cells would prove that the two men of the escort that night were not there, but out of service and far from the Torrino area. After a few days the Aisi launched another track: the two could be more trivially known to law enforcement agencies.&nbsp;
